{"questionId":"9118053","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>An economist advises the government of Country A to spend $207 million on a new infrastructure project. She estimates that as a result, nominal GDP would increase by $828 million, <em>ceteris paribus</em>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Calculate the estimated value of the multiplier used by the economist.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p>0.75 <em>is sufficient for <strong>[1]</strong></em>.</p>\n<p>OFR applies.</p>","meta":{"questionId":"9118053","referenceCode":"20N.3.HL.TZ0.2e.ii","subjectId":"48-dp-economics","title":"Calculate the estimated value of the multiplier used by the economist.","paper":"3","level":"HL","questionNumber":"e.ii","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["First exams 2022","Last exams 2021","Last exams 2021","Section 2: Macroeconomics","First exams 2022","Unit 3: Macroeconomics","3.6 Demand management—fiscal policy","3.6.4 Keynesian multiplier","First exams 2022","Unit 3: Macroeconomics","3.6 Demand management—fiscal policy","First exams 2022","Unit 3: Macroeconomics","Last exams 2021","Section 2: Macroeconomics","2.2 Aggregate demand and aggregate supply","The Keynesian multiplier","The nature of the Keynesian multiplier","Last exams 2021","Section 2: Macroeconomics","2.2 Aggregate demand and aggregate supply","The Keynesian multiplier","Last exams 2021","Section 2: Macroeconomics","2.2 Aggregate demand and aggregate supply"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}